    "description": {
      "es": "",
      "en": "Field objects describe each defined field. These objects are created internally, and are returned by the fields() module-level method (see below). Users should never instantiate a Field object directly. Its documented attributes are: name: The name of the field. type: The type of the field. default, default_factory, init, repr, hash, compare, metadata, and kw_only have the identical meaning and values as they do in the field() function. Other attributes may exist, but they are private and mus..."
